459
00:26:01,196 --> 00:26:03,219
However, amidst this hunger for power,

460
00:26:03,219 --> 00:26:06,378
there is a positive legacy 
left by Napoleon worth noting.

461
00:26:06,378 --> 00:26:11,836
Several decisions he made had far-reaching 
benefits for the future of France and Europe.

462
00:26:11,836 --> 00:26:14,464
The Napoleonic Code of 1804

463
00:26:14,464 --> 00:26:17,618
stands out as a landmark legal framework, providing France 

464
00:26:17,618 --> 00:26:20,338
with a comprehensive and written set of laws.

465
00:26:20,338 --> 00:26:22,720
The second achievement was the establishment 
of equality for males under the law,

466
00:26:22,720 --> 00:26:24,774
despite the setbacks for women's rights

467
00:26:24,774 --> 00:26:26,929
and the reintroduction of slavery.

468
00:26:26,929 --> 00:26:31,181
The equal rights given to the male citizens by the law,

469
00:26:31,181 --> 00:26:32,365
remained unchanged.

470
00:26:32,365 --> 00:26:36,208
Furthermore, Napoleon's era marked 
the end of feudalism in France,

471
00:26:36,208 --> 00:26:38,886
In the territories he occupied,

472
00:26:38,886 --> 00:26:41,441
the same laws were enforced.

473
00:26:41,441 --> 00:26:43,374
Third, Secularism.

474
00:26:43,374 --> 00:26:45,952
During Napoleon's rule, the French 
government adopted a secular stance. 

475
00:26:45,952 --> 00:26:47,788
There was religious freedom in France,

476
00:26:47,788 --> 00:26:51,355
allowing individuals to practice their chosen religions.

477
00:26:51,355 --> 00:26:55,215
In 1801, Christianity did return to France

478
00:26:55,215 --> 00:26:58,057
when Napoleon signed an agreement with the Pope.

479
00:26:58,057 --> 00:27:01,191
But the relationship between the Church and the Government

480
00:27:01,191 --> 00:27:02,719
never fully went back to the way it used to be.

481
00:27:02,719 --> 00:27:06,628
The power balance shifted more favourably towards the government.

482
00:27:06,628 --> 00:27:11,905
While traditional positions of the 
Catholic clergy in the Church were restored,

483
00:27:11,905 --> 00:27:16,826
the government retained control over the selection of bishops

484
00:27:16,826 --> 00:27:21,529
and supervised the church's finances,

485
00:27:21,529 --> 00:27:25,802
significantly diminishing the influence 
of the church in European affairs.

486
00:27:25,802 --> 00:27:28,947
Fourth, establishing a banking system.

487
00:27:28,947 --> 00:27:33,111
The Bank of France was founded by Napoleon in 1800,

488
00:27:33,111 --> 00:27:36,595
It brought hyperinflation under control

489
00:27:36,595 --> 00:27:38,481
and stabilized the currency.

490
00:27:38,481 --> 00:27:42,304
Fifth, he introduced a modern and efficient tax system,

491
00:27:42,304 --> 00:27:46,266
ending the exemptions previously granted to nobility and kings,

492
00:27:46,266 --> 00:27:51,680
ensuring that everyone contributed to the tax base.

493
00:27:51,680 --> 00:27:53,814
Sixth, in the education system,

494
00:27:53,814 --> 00:27:55,560
Napoleon set up primary, secondary, and high schools,

495
00:27:55,560 --> 00:27:58,332
along with establishing the University of France.

496
00:27:58,332 --> 00:28:00,632
Uniformity was introduced to the education system,

497
00:28:00,632 --> 00:28:02,306
teachers were trained,

